issues.title: Short Nose Crankshaft Failure
issues.description: 1990-1991 NA Miatas have a shorter crankshaft nose that can break off, causing catastrophic engine failure. The keyway on the crank nose is too shallow and the pulley can slip, leading to timing issues and potential crank failure.
issues.fix_description: Replace crankshaft with longer nose version from 1992+ models, replace timing belt, and inspect for damage
issues.prevention: Regular timing belt maintenance, avoid over-torquing crank pulley, check for pulley wobble

issues.title: Timing Belt Failure
issues.description: The interference engine design means timing belt failure results in valve damage. Belt typically fails every 60,000-90,000 miles if not replaced preventively.
issues.fix_description: Replace timing belt, water pump, tensioner, and repair valve damage if present
issues.prevention: Replace timing belt every 60,000 miles or 5 years, inspect regularly for cracking

issues.title: Rear Main Seal Leak
issues.description: Common oil leak from rear main seal, especially on higher mileage vehicles. Can cause significant oil loss and clutch contamination.
issues.fix_description: Remove transmission and replace rear main seal, inspect flywheel surface
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, avoid overfilling oil, replace PCV valve

issues.title: Power Steering Rack Failure
issues.description: Power steering rack develops internal leaks and excessive play, causing steering issues and fluid leaks.
issues.fix_description: Replace power steering rack or rebuild existing unit
issues.prevention: Regular power steering fluid changes, avoid hitting curbs

issues.title: Clutch Master/Slave Cylinder Failure
issues.description: Hydraulic clutch system components fail, causing clutch pedal to go to floor or become spongy.
issues.fix_description: Replace master cylinder, slave cylinder, and bleed system
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes, inspect for leaks periodically

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: Plastic door handle mechanisms break internally, making it difficult or impossible to open doors from outside.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle mechanism and outer handle
issues.prevention: Gentle operation of door handles, regular lubrication

issues.title: Soft Top Frame Cracking
issues.description: Aluminum soft top frame develops cracks at stress points, particularly around the rear window area.
issues.fix_description: Weld cracks or replace soft top frame assembly
issues.prevention: Avoid forcing top operation, regular lubrication of hinges

issues.title: Differential Pinion Seal Leak
issues.description: Pinion seal in rear differential leaks gear oil, especially common on higher mileage vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Replace pinion seal and refill with proper gear oil
issues.prevention: Regular differential service, avoid overloading vehicle

issues.title: Window Regulator Failure
issues.description: Manual window regulators wear out, causing windows to fall down or become difficult to operate.
issues.fix_description: Replace window regulator mechanism and lubricate tracks
issues.prevention: Regular lubrication of window tracks, gentle operation

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: In-tank fuel pump fails, particularly on higher mileage vehicles, causing fuel delivery issues.
symptoms: Engine cuts out at highway speeds
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump assembly and fuel filter
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank above 1/4 full, replace fuel filter regularly

issues.title: Heater Core Failure
issues.description: Heater core develops internal leaks, causing coolant loss and fogged windows.
issues.fix_description: Replace heater core, requires dashboard removal
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, flush cooling system periodically

issues.title: Brake Master Cylinder Failure
issues.description: Brake master cylinder internal seals fail, causing brake pedal to go to floor and loss of braking power.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake master cylinder and bleed brake system
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes, inspect brake system annually

editorial.tagline: Pure roadster joy in its most honest form
editorial.hero_blurb: The original NA Miata proved that driving bliss doesn't require exotic badges or overwhelming power. This is the car that revived the lightweight roadster formula with Japanese reliability and an irrepressible spirit that transforms every drive into an occasion.
editorial.essence: The NA Miata distills the roadster experience to its absolute essence: lightweight construction, perfect balance, and an engine that loves to rev. It's a car that makes you feel like a driving hero whether you're navigating a mountain pass or simply running errands around town.
editorial.heritage: Launched in 1989 as Mazda's love letter to British roadsters like the Lotus Elan, the NA Miata single-handedly revived the affordable sports car segment. Drawing inspiration from classic proportions and modern reliability, it established the template that countless manufacturers would follow.
editorial.design_philosophy: Jinba ittai - the unity of horse and rider. Mazda's designers obsessed over weight distribution, low center of gravity, and intuitive controls to create a car that responds to your thoughts before your hands move the wheel.
editorial.motorsport_history: The NA became an instant grassroots racing legend, dominating autocross events and club racing series. Its balanced chassis and aftermarket support made it the weapon of choice for weekend warriors and professional drivers alike in spec racing series worldwide.
editorial.engine_character: The twin-cam engines are eager and sweet-spinning, building power smoothly to redline with a satisfying mechanical urgency. While not brutally powerful, they deliver their output with enthusiasm and beg to be worked through the rev range.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 5-speed manual is a masterclass in shifter feel - short throws, crisp gates, and perfect weighting that makes every gear change a tactile pleasure. It's the transmission that taught a generation what good shifting should feel like.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Beautifully balanced with near-perfect weight distribution, the chassis is forgiving at the limit yet eager to rotate. It rewards smooth inputs while maintaining composure even when pushed hard, making novices feel like heroes and experts appreciate its honesty.
editorial.steering_feel: Direct, communicative, and perfectly weighted recirculating ball steering that builds resistance naturally with cornering loads. Every undulation in the road surface telegraphs through the wheel, creating an intimate connection between driver and tarmac.
editorial.brake_confidence: While not overwhelmingly powerful, the brakes are progressive and confidence-inspiring with good pedal feel. They're well-matched to the car's modest weight and performance envelope, providing reliable stopping power for spirited driving.
editorial.sound_signature: A characterful growl that builds to an excited buzz at high RPM, punctuated by the satisfying mechanical symphony of valvetrain noise. The exhaust note is purposeful without being obnoxious, with a distinctly Japanese four-cylinder character.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who value engagement over straight-line speed, weekend canyon carvers, autocross enthusiasts, and anyone seeking an authentic connection to their car. Perfect for those who understand that smiles per gallon matter more than horsepower per dollar.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Daily drivers needing cargo space or weather protection, power-hungry enthusiasts seeking acceleration thrills, or those requiring modern safety features and conveniences. The minimalist approach isn't for everyone.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for rust around wheel wells and door frames, especially on early cars. Maintenance history matters more than mileage - a well-cared-for high-mileage example often beats a neglected garage queen. Values are climbing, so don't wait too long.

expertReviews.title: Is It Worth The Hype? NA Mazda Miata Review
pros: Lightweight and pure driving experience
Perfect balance between comfort and sportiness
Reliable and less maintenance than British roadsters
Wide appeal - can cruise or attack corners
Timeless fun that never gets old
Turns heads and gets positive attention
Good investment potential - past depreciation
Makes driving everywhere feel like an adventure
cons: Headlight mechanism issues (goes up/down endlessly)
Rough idle when warm after short stops
Stock suspension transitions are sloppy for sliding
Power steering can fail
30-year-old car requires ongoing maintenance
Low power requires wringing it out to keep up
expertReviews.verdict: The NA Miata is described as the 'derivative of what makes driving fun' - a momentum car that provides all the sensations of much faster cars but in slow motion, allowing more time to savor the experience. The reviewer considers it more fun than any other car driven, from budget enthusiast cars to exotic supercars. The 1995 M Edition with its unique burgundy color, BBS wheels, and limited production makes it the reviewer's perfect first-gen Miata. While it has typical 30-year-old car quirks, it's praised for proving the business case for affordable roadsters and changing the sports car market.

expertReviews.title: 1992 Mazda MX-5 Miata (NA) | Is It Still Relevant Nowadays?
pros: Excellent manual transmission with short throws
Lightweight at 2200 lbs with great proportions
Pop-up headlights and timeless classic design
Very communicative chassis and steering feedback
Fun and playful driving character
Clean 60k mile example with pristine interior
cons: Brakes are not a strength even after refresh
Limited space for taller drivers (6'1+ challenging)
Some slop in steering rack with accuracy issues
Heel-toe downshifting difficult with larger feet
Complex manual soft top operation
Rust issues from Indiana road salt
expertReviews.verdict: The NA Miata remains highly relevant as a pure driving experience. With thoughtful modifications including coilovers, sway bars, wheels/tires, and brake refresh, this example transforms from sketchy when stock to planted and confidence-inspiring. The 5-speed manual transmission is exceptional even by modern standards, and the lightweight character creates a playful, whimsical driving experience. While not powerful, the 1.6L naturally aspirated engine encourages rev-happy driving. Perfect weekend car that puts a smile on your face.

expertReviews.title: Here's Why the NA Mazda Miata Is a Sports Car Icon
pros: Incredibly lightweight at under 2200 lbs
Simple and pure sports car design
Easy manual convertible top operation
Modern Japanese reliability compared to old British roadsters
Revolutionary revival of the two-seat roadster segment
cons: Very basic interior with manual everything
Limited power at 115 hp from 1.6L engine
Extremely small size limits practicality
No storage space or comfort features
Slow acceleration with 0-60 in around 9 seconds
expertReviews.verdict: The 1990 NA Miata is a legendary sports car icon that successfully revived the two-seat roadster segment with modern reliability. While lacking in power and luxury features, its lightweight design, simplicity, and pure driving experience made it a smash hit that defined the modern roadster template.

expertReviews.title: 1990 Mazda Miata Review - Yuri Bought for $1
pros: Excellent shifter feel

expertReviews.verdict: Classic NA Miata delivers the quintessential roadster experience with excellent shifter feel and go-kart handling, but 116hp makes it very slow by modern standards. Perfect for enthusiasts who prioritize driving engagement over straight-line speed.

expertReviews.title: Should You Buy a NA Mazda Miata?
pros: Extremely fun to drive
Great handling and drifting capability
Lightweight at 2300 lbs
Reliable - can reach 300k miles with care
Reasonable maintenance costs
Great looks
Easy to drive like a go-kart
cons: Very rough and bumpy suspension
Poor AC performance

Engine sputtering issue when hot

expertReviews.verdict: The NA Miata is not practical, comfortable, or fast, but it's incredibly fun to drive and great value at $10k. Perfect for those prioritizing driving enjoyment over comfort. Choose 1.6L for modding/tracking, 1.8L for stock daily use. Reliable but expect a rough daily driving experience.

expertReviews.title: Mazda MX-5 NA (Miata NA) Review | Rusty Death Trap or ...
pros: Brilliant handling and connected driving experience
Perfect 50/50 weight distribution makes it predictable
Excellent short-throw gearbox with engaging gear shifts
Simple manual convertible top operation
Linear power delivery with responsive throttle
Good rear-wheel drive feel for sporty driving
Iconic pop-up headlights provide character
Quick-revving 1.8L engine that sounds decent
Can be used as a daily driver with reasonable practicality
cons: Severe rust issues affecting body panels, sills and subframes
Heavy steering at low speeds due to no power steering
Interior shows age with lots of plastic and basic materials
Limited storage space and practicality
Brakes could be better and lack ABS
Indicator stalk on wrong side for non-Japanese markets
Lacks power compared to modern turbocharged cars
Poor boot space in grand scheme of things
expertReviews.verdict: The NA MX-5 is described as an 'absolute gem' that represents the pinnacle of connected, back-to-basics driving. Despite common rust issues and dated interior, it delivers brilliant handling with perfect weight distribution and an engaging driving experience. The reviewer wholeheartedly recommends it for driving enthusiasts who can find a good example, noting it successfully achieved Mazda's goal of creating a reliable British roadster alternative with excellent chassis dynamics and rear-wheel drive engagement.
